cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically image classification and super-resolution, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for reducing the number of parameters in convolutional neural networks, which is a common problem in deep learning and suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also involves training the network to learn a basis for the filters, which is a form of unsupervised learning, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on image benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
